Hereafter books can only be withdrawn from the shelves as follows : A card must be filled out by the student, stating the number of volumes desired, with their titles and authors. This card is presented to the librarian who will find the books, and when the student is through with them, they must be brought to the libra- rian's desk, when the application card will be returned. Officers and students may withdraw for their own use, out side the library, any library book except reference and rare books, subject to the following restrictions. (a) No student may have more than two books out at the same time. (b) No student may keep a book out more than seYen days, but a withdrawal may be re- newed by the librarian for an additional seven days.
